wikipedia_page.main: Sir James Douglas Cooke, FRCS (1879 – 13 July 1949) was a Conservative politician from England. He served as the British Conservative politician for Hammersmith South In 1931, he became a member of Parliament, where he remained until 1945. He was knighted in the Queen's Birthday Honours list in 1945.

response: * James Douglas Cooke (1879–1949), British Member of Parliament for Hammersmith South
